INSERT INTO post
(title, alias, description, content, publish_date, author_id, category_id, cover_id, status_id)
VALUES(
    'PS5 user Can Now Sign Up to Test New Features Early',
    'ps5-user-can-now-sign-up-to-test-new-features-early',
    'Registrations are now open for the PS5 System Software Beta Program.',
    '<p>If you are one of the lucky ones that managed to get a <a href="/games/playstation-5">PS5</a> between now and when the system launched last November, you can now sign up to become a tester in the <a target="_blank" href="https://blog.playstation.com/2021/06/17/sign-up-for-the-first-ps5-system-software-beta-program/" rel="noopener noreferrer">inaugural PS5 system software beta program</a>. </p><div class="jsx-2483022842 adunit-wrapper"><div id="3631192" class="jsx-2483022842 bobble bobble-0"><div class="jsx-2180275872"><div class="jsx-2180275872 slot-container blocked"><div id="slot-mediumAd-1631259855922" data-slot-info="{}" class="jsx-2180275872 slot-element"></div></div></div></div></div><p>According to <a target="_blank" href="https://blog.playstation.com/2021/06/17/sign-up-for-the-first-ps5-system-software-beta-program/" rel="noopener noreferrer">the latest PlayStation Blog</a>, testers that sign up and are selected will be "among the first to put new features to the test and provide essential feedback that will help guide [Sony''s] development." </p><p>That means you''ll get early access to the next firmware update for the PS5 ahead of its public release, and share your thoughts on the firmware to help Sony improve on anything that needs tweaking. It''s not unlike the <a target="_blank" href="https://www.xbox.com/legal/insider-program" rel="noopener noreferrer">Xbox Insider Program</a>, which regularly tests upcoming features with a sub-set of Xbox user.</p><output class="article-video-container"><div class="jsx-283099997 jsx-2147466702 video-wrapper"><div class="jsx-283099997 jsx-2147466702 video-container"><div class="jsx-3905315446 aspect-ratio-container aspect-ratio-16-9"><div class="jsx-3905315446 aspect-ratio-child"><div class="jsx-3424665568 player idle"><div class="jsx-190022862 ad-wrapper hidden"><div role="presentation" class="jsx-190022862 click-blocker hidden"><div class="jsx-190022862 advertisement-label"></div><div class="jsx-190022862 learn-more">Learn More</div></div><div class="jsx-190022862 video-ad"><div class="jsx-190022862 loading-container animation-default"><div class="jsx-190022862 loading-now-playing animation-default">Now playing</div><div class="jsx-190022862 loading-title animation-default">PlayStation''s Year in Review</div><div class="jsx-190022862 loading-poster"><div class="jsx-190022862 loading-anim animation-default"></div><div class="jsx-190022862 loading-blur-anim animation-default"></div></div></div></div><div class="jsx-190022862 ad-controls hidden"><div role="presentation" aria-label="play pause toggle" class="jsx-190022862 play playing"></div><div class="jsx-402112792 volume-slider-container"><div role="presentation" class="jsx-402112792 volume-speaker low-volume muted"></div></div></div><div class="jsx-190022862 ad-progress hidden"><div class="jsx-190022862 current-progress" style="width: 0%; transition: width 350ms linear 0s;"></div>;</div></div><video playsinline="" preload="metadata" tabindex="0" crossorigin="anonymous" data-title="PlayStation''s Year in Review" thumbnail="https://assets1.ignimgs.com/thumbs/userUploaded/2021/6/11/playstationsyearinreview36190303yearinreviewplaystationblogroll-1623443283141.jpg" identifier="b3d77f7b4b57c551a5242f779d586845" live="false" class="jsx-1906181548 " src="blob:https://www.ign.com/e2762603-ed43-4b6d-a64e-a4114e7ca210"></video><div class="jsx-4260723406 video-overlay show-background"><div class="jsx-1855809287 video-header show"><a href="https://www.ign.com/videos/2021/06/11/playstations-year-in-review" class="jsx-1855809287 title">PlayStation''s Year in Review</a></div><div class="jsx-2530077071 poster-container"><div role="presentation" class="jsx-2530077071 play"></div><div class="jsx-2530077071 duration">8:59</div><div role="presentation" class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-container"><div class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-message"><div class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-toggle"><div class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-icon on"></div></div><span class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-text"><span class="jsx-1965293124 text-left">Autoplay setting: </span><span class="jsx-1965293124 text-right">On</span></span></div></div></div><div role="presentation" hidden="" class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-container"><div class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-message"><div class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-toggle"><div class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-icon on"></div></div><span class="jsx-1965293124 autoplay-text"><span class="jsx-1965293124 text-left">Autoplay setting: </span><span class="jsx-1965293124 text-right">On</span></span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></output><p>If you are interested in beta testing the next PS5 firmware update, you can <a target="_blank" href="https://www.playstation.com/ps5/ps5-beta-program-sign-up" rel="noopener noreferrer">sign up now on the official PlayStation website</a>. You must be 18 years of age and reside in the US, Canada, Japan, UK, Germany, or France to be considered. This is nothing hugely new for the company, as the <a href="/articles/2017/01/12/sign-up-now-to-beta-test-the-next-big-ps4-update">PS4 also allowed people to sign up for a system software beta program</a> to test out the software before a console update would roll out. </p><section class="jsx-535847410 object-feedback article-object-feedback-component article-object-feedback-embed"><div class="jsx-1417596211 feedback-container"><div class="jsx-1417596211 feedback-content"><p id="feedback-question" class="jsx-1417596211 feedback-question">Have you played PlayStation 5?</p><div role="group" aria-labelledby="feedback-question" class="jsx-1417596211 feedback-buttons"><button type="button" class="jsx-237381145 button button--secondary large">YES</button><button type="button" class="jsx-237381145 button button--secondary large">NO</button></div></div></div></section><p>The <a href="/articles/first-major-ps5-update-coming-tomorrow-allows-ps5-games-to-be-stored-on-usb-drives#:~:text=As%20revealed%20on%20the%20PlayStation,Trophy%20Settings%20and%20Stats%20screen.">PS5''s last major update</a> introduces several new features to the console, such as cross-generation Share Play and extending USB storage, allowing you to store (albeit not play) PS5 games stored on a USB external drive. </p><div class="divider-container"><hr class="accent-divider"></div><p><em>Taylor is the Associate Tech Editor at IGN. You can follow her on Twitter </em><a target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/TayNixster" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>@TayNixster</em></a><em>.</em></p>',
    '2021-06-17 18:05', 4, 2, ( SELECT id FROM post_cover WHERE filename = '06' LIMIT 1 ), 201);

